headline: NVR (NVR) Margin Miss Challenges High Quality Narrative as Valuation Premium Widens
summary: NVR (NVR) posted earnings that have climbed at an average annual rate of 10.8% over the past five years, but the company faced negative earnings growth in the most recent period. Net profit margins narrowed to 14.2%, down from 16.2% last year, even as NVR's earnings remain categorized as high quality. With valuation now a prominent discussion point, investors are balancing the company's historical track record with the reality of shrinking profitability and shares trading at a premium to...
